fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.types

Interface IDateData

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IData<IDateType>

    public interface IDateData
extends IData<IDateType>
    Provides typed access to date data for a cell. Values should be exchanged with the connector in the UTC time zone.

    The data value is of type Date. The value may be set using Date or Long.

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • getMsecDateValue

        long getMsecDateValue()
        Gets the date value as a number of milliseconds relative to the Unix Epoch time. The milliseconds for the time of day are set to midnight (00:00:00.000) for the UTC timezone.

        Note: NULL values are coerced to 0.

        Returns:
        true if the value is true, or false if the value is false or null.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getValue()

      • setMsecDateValue

        void setMsecDateValue(long value)
        Sets the date value as a number of milliseconds relative to the Unix Epoch time.

        Note: you cannot set a NULL value using this method. Use setValue instead.

        Parameters:
        value - value to set, as a number of milliseconds relative to the Unix Epoch time. Any milliseconds for the time of day (for the UTC timezone) are discarded.
        Since:
        1.0
